    "recap_headline": "Ohio State Buckeyes | Ohio State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SEATTLE, Wash.\n\u2013 The Ohio State baseball team (6-10, 1-3 Big Ten) earned its Big Ten win of the season, defeating Washington (6-11, 2-2 Big Ten), 10-9, in 10 innings.\nGame Recap\nThe Huskies struck first, taking a 1-0 lead after scoring on a Buckeye error in the bottom of the second inning.\nCJ Reid\ndrew a walk to lead off the top of the third, followed by an infield bunt single from\nMiles Vandenheuvel\nto put two runners on. A sacrifice bunt from\nLee Ellis\nadvanced both runners.\nHenry Kaczmar\nstepped up to the dish next, doubling down the right field line to send both runners home and give the Buckeyes the lead, 2-1.\nIn the bottom of the fourth, the Huskies tied the score, 2-2, after a solo home run.\nWith two outs in the top of the fifth inning, Kaczmar walked. A double to left field from\nNoah Furcht\nsent Kaczmar home and put the Buckeyes back in the lead, 3-2, and an RBI single from\nMason Eckelman\nand an RBI double from\nAlex Bemis\nextended the lead, 5-2.\nIn the top of the sixth, with two outs,\nMiles Vandenheuvel\ntripled to right field. He scored on a Washington error to give the Buckeyes a four-run lead, 6-2.\nA solo home run and a two-run home run from the Huskies in the bottom of the sixth cut the Ohio State lead to one, 6-5.\nIn the top of the seventh, Bemis was walked. A double to deep center field from\nDane Harvey\nsent Bemis home and put Ohio State ahead by two, 7-5.\nIn the bottom of the seventh, a solo home run and a score on a Buckeye error for the Huskies tied the score, 7-7.\nReid led off with a single through the right side in the eighth inning, and advanced to second on a wild pitch. With one out, Ellis singled through the right side, advancing Reid to third to put runners on the corners. A sacrifice bunt from Kaczmar sent Reid home and a single from Furcht scored Ellis to put the Buckeyes back ahead, 9-7.\nIn the bottom of the eighth, the Huskies scored on back-to-back Ohio State errors to tie the score once again, 9-9.\nIn the bottom of the ninth with two runners on the Huskies,\nJake Michalak\nfanned two and an impressive play by Ellis to Reid at first ended the inning, sending the game into a 10\nth\ninning.\nIn the top of the 10\nth\nwith two outs on the board, Ellis came up big for the Buckeyes, sending one out of the park in left field to put the Buckeyes back on top, 10-9.\nIn the bottom of the 10\nth\ninning, one runner reached for the Huskies with two outs, but a pitcher to first base groundout ended the inning and secured the 10-9 victory for the Buckeyes.\nBuckeyes by the Numbers\nThe Buckeyes totaled 13 hits. Ellis, Kaczmar, Furcht, Harvey and Vandenheuvel each had two hits.\nKaczmar had a team-high three RBIs.\nGavin Kuzniewski\nfanned four and gave up five runs on seven hits in 5.2 innings pitched.\nMichalak (2-0) earned the win on the mound. He struck out three and allowed two runs on four hits in 3.0 innings pitched.\nUp Next\nThe Buckeyes and Huskies continue their series with games on Saturday, March 14 at 10 p.m. ET and Sunday, March 15 at 4 p.m. ET.\n#GoBucks"
